Title: Piano Concerto No. 2 in F Major, Op. 102: II. Andante
Album: Shostakovich: Piano Concertos Nos. 1 & 2 - Poulenc: Concerto for 2 Pianos, FP 61
Artist(s): Dmitri Shostakovich, Leonard Bernstein, New York Philharmonic
Comment: My mixtape rule #1 used to be to never include a tracklist. So I always kept handwritten tracklists for reference, and today I went and unearthed a cache of lists from mixtapes I'd made in my twenties. This track was at the end of a mix cassette for a colleague and out-of-my-league crush, and also contained Yeah Yeah Yeahs, Radiohead, and various excepts from 1950s radio play "Under Milk Wood". You're going to find this hard to believe, but - we didn't get together (but we are still friends).
